When I was in Bangkok,

282
00:24:23,326 --> 00:24:25,646
if I got hungry, I could just walk down to 7-Eleven.

283
00:24:25,926 --> 00:24:28,606
But here, there aren’t any stores open at all.

284
00:24:28,806 --> 00:24:30,646
And you want me to wake up Uncle Chit?

285
00:24:30,966 --> 00:24:32,326
I can’t do it.

286
00:24:32,726 --> 00:24:34,446
I was so hungry!

287
00:24:36,206 --> 00:24:38,326
Then tonight, before we head back to our stay,

288
00:24:38,966 --> 00:24:40,486
let's buy some food to stock up.

289
00:24:41,166 --> 00:24:42,366
Eat quickly!

290
00:24:53,806 --> 00:24:55,246
This shop is really delicious!

291
00:25:05,646 --> 00:25:07,726
[ttamanusorn Wooden Bridge]

292
00:25:22,046 --> 00:25:24,846
Hello Ryu, Hello Arm.

293
00:25:25,406 --> 00:25:26,646
Hi Din.

294
00:25:26,646 --> 00:25:27,646
Um, where...

295
00:25:27,646 --> 00:25:31,246
Oh, Mangkon is stuck in a meeting, so he sent me instead.

296
00:25:32,406 --> 00:25:36,686
Anyway, please take care of Din today. Shall we go then

297
00:25:36,806 --> 00:25:38,006
Sure!

298
00:25:38,366 --> 00:25:39,406
But

299
00:25:39,926 --> 00:25:43,326
I think since you two have come all the way here,

300
00:25:43,806 --> 00:25:46,046
you should try to blend in with the locals a bit.

301
00:26:21,581 --> 00:26:23,181
How was it Din, am I look handsome?

302
00:26:25,781 --> 00:26:27,181
You are so handsome!

303
00:26:28,941 --> 00:26:29,861
Of course!

304
00:26:29,861 --> 00:26:31,781
พี่ใส่อะไรก็ดูดีอยู่แล้วล่ะ!

305
00:26:32,981 --> 00:26:33,781
Um...

306
00:26:35,701 --> 00:26:37,541
Boss! come out.

307
00:27:18,141 --> 00:27:19,461
What’s wrong boss?

308
00:27:19,701 --> 00:27:20,941
You look like you need to poop.

309
00:27:24,501 --> 00:27:25,861
I never do something like this.

310
00:27:26,901 --> 00:27:29,061
Wow, you're not that young anymore.

311
00:27:29,181 --> 00:27:30,741
Try doing something different for once.

312
00:27:34,301 --> 00:27:35,461
Come, come, look that.

313
00:27:35,861 --> 00:27:37,461
These are all so beautiful!

314
00:27:38,021 --> 00:27:38,941
Yes!

315
00:27:38,941 --> 00:27:41,461
Especially during festivals, the bridge gets really crowded.

316
00:27:41,861 --> 00:27:42,621
Wow.

317
00:27:42,621 --> 00:27:44,621
With so many people, won't the bridge break?

318
00:27:44,821 --> 00:27:45,781
No, it won’t break.

319
00:27:45,781 --> 00:27:47,141
Here, we have a team that takes care of the maintenance

320
00:27:47,301 --> 00:27:48,581
and improvements all the time,

321
00:27:48,581 --> 00:27:49,661
so don't worry!

322
00:27:50,221 --> 00:27:51,541
The place where we are standing right now

323
00:27:51,541 --> 00:27:52,661
is called the Mon Bridge,

324
00:27:52,741 --> 00:27:55,301
or it is also known as the Uttamanusorn Bridge.

325
00:27:55,501 --> 00:27:58,181
It is the longest wooden bridge in Thailand,

326
00:27:58,341 --> 00:28:00,741
with a length of 850 meters.

327
00:28:01,781 --> 00:28:05,341
So why is there a wooden bridge in Thailand?

328
00:28:05,381 --> 00:28:07,341
But the name is of Burmese origin.

329
00:28:07,941 --> 00:28:10,221
Ah, the word "Songkalia"

330
00:28:10,221 --> 00:28:11,581
is in the Mon language.

331
00:28:11,581 --> 00:28:12,541
It means that in the past,

332
00:28:12,981 --> 00:28:14,541
there was no border division

333
00:28:14,541 --> 00:28:15,781
like there is today between the two sides.

334
00:28:16,021 --> 00:28:18,381
This allowed both the Burmese and Mon people

335
00:28:18,381 --> 00:28:19,901
to visit each other across both sides.

336
00:28:19,981 --> 00:28:22,581
As we know, driving there only takes a short while.

337
00:28:22,621 --> 00:28:24,181
We would have reached Myanmar by now.

338
00:28:24,181 --> 00:28:28,621
This has led to a blending of languages and cultures.

339
00:28:29,101 --> 00:28:30,341
In the morning.

340
00:28:30,581 --> 00:28:32,101
There will be a alms-giving ceremony,

341
00:28:32,101 --> 00:28:34,901
and tourists like to participate in it.

342
00:28:35,261 --> 00:28:38,861
Some tourists choose to stay here.

343
00:28:38,981 --> 00:28:41,101
So that they don't have to drive up here,

344
00:28:41,101 --> 00:28:43,021
there are various types of accommodations available.

345
00:28:43,261 --> 00:28:44,061
For example hotel

346
00:28:44,141 --> 00:28:44,941
resort

347
00:28:45,261 --> 00:28:47,181
The prices are according to one's budget.

348
00:28:47,381 --> 00:28:49,061
If you have the chance next time,

349
00:28:49,181 --> 00:28:51,221
feel free to come up and join the almsgiving.

350
00:29:24,221 --> 00:29:25,661
How long you going to stay here?

351
00:29:27,341 --> 00:29:29,381
Would you like the work pass?

352
00:29:31,941 --> 00:29:32,741
Of course!

353
00:29:35,061 --> 00:29:36,221
Of course, boss!

354
00:29:37,181 --> 00:29:38,581
This is for you.

355
00:29:42,301 --> 00:29:43,581
What wrong with you?

356
00:29:44,461 --> 00:29:45,101
Ouch!

357
00:29:45,101 --> 00:29:47,221
I don't have any attraction towards the boss.

358
00:29:47,381 --> 00:29:48,981
It just so happens that someone brought it to sell,

359
00:29:48,981 --> 00:29:50,981
and I helped buy it.

360
00:29:51,381 --> 00:29:53,181
I was going to throw it away, but it felt like a waste.

361
00:29:53,181 --> 00:29:54,941
Here, just take it.

362
00:29:59,981 --> 00:30:02,501
Let's go, I'll take you to the boat.

363
00:30:02,701 --> 00:30:04,981
The boat?

364
00:31:20,381 --> 00:31:21,181
Cheers!

365
00:31:28,901 --> 00:31:32,061
Today, I have to thank Mongkorn very much

366
00:31:32,141 --> 00:31:33,541
